comment: A administrator had created a BMLT meeting format with trailing whitespace. GetSearchResults (jsonp) returns the format string for a meeting using this format as: ` "formats": "C,LGBTQI ,NC,GB", ` However the GetFormats call does not return the trailing whitespace. ``` { "key_string": "LGBTQI", "name_string": "LGBTQI", "description_string": "This meeting is focused on the needs of Lesbian, Gay, Bisexual, Transgender, Queer and Intersex members of NA.", "lang": "en", "id": "10", "world_id": "GL", "root_server_uri": "https://na.org.au/main_server", "format_type_enum": "FC3" } ``` This causes lookups based on a simple 'split format string by comma' to fail. Whilst this can be worked around on the client side, ideally we'd sanitise on input to prevent this from occuring (if not a historical issue).
